    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-burgers-with-smashed-caesar-chicken-and-bacon/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons </strong>and cook for 8-9 min or until very crispy</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-burgers-with-smashed-caesar-chicken-and-bacon/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Roughly shred <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lettuce</strong> and very finely slice the <strong>remaining lettuce</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>into rounds</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-burgers-with-smashed-caesar-chicken-and-bacon/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> in a large bowl with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, a little <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!), and a <strong>pinch</strong> of your <strong>dried oregano</strong> </p><p>Add a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sugar </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>caesar dressing</strong> </p><p>Transfer 1 tsp per person of <strong>dressing</strong> to a small bowl and set aside for later, then add the <strong>finely shredded lettuce</strong> to the <strong>remaining dressing</strong> with the <strong>crispy bacon lardons </strong>(reserve the pan!) and toss \u2013 this is your <strong>bacon caesar salad topping</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-burgers-with-smashed-caesar-chicken-and-bacon/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>chicken mince</strong> and <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> in a large bowl with the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> remaining dried oregano </strong>and your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Mix until very well combined, then equally divide and shape into 2 rough meatballs per person</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-burgers-with-smashed-caesar-chicken-and-bacon/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong></p><p>Press them down very firmly with an <strong>oiled </strong>spatula (this will stop them sticking!) and cook for 4-5 min on each side, or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 these are your <strong>smashed patties</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-burgers-with-smashed-caesar-chicken-and-bacon/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the smashed patties are cooked through, set aside to rest until serving</p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half (if required!)</p><p>Once the fries are ready, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the<strong> brioche halves </strong>(cut side up!) on top of the fries</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 2-3 min or until slightly toasted</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-burgers-with-smashed-caesar-chicken-and-bacon/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>toasted brioche base</strong> with the <strong>sliced tomato</strong>,<strong> 2 smashed patties</strong>,<strong> </strong>the <strong>bacon caesar salad topping </strong>and the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, then the <strong>brioche lid </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> smashed chicken & bacon caesar burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>roughly shredded lettuce </strong>to the side and drizzle over the<strong> reserved dressing</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> fries</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
